A split-screen vintage 1950s style illustration showing the same cluttered living room in two states: on the left, a chaotic mess of furniture, newspapers, lamps, and decorative objects scattered haphazardly with no organization, colors muted and muddy; on the right, the identical room transformed into an elegant, harmonious space where the same objects are artfully arranged with perfect balance, warm cohesive colors, and clear visual hierarchy. The contrast is dramatic yet both sides share the same retro mid-century aesthetic with rounded furniture shapes, atomic-age decorative elements, and a muted palette of teals, oranges, and creams. A dotted line divides the two halves. The illustration evokes the feeling of transformation through organization and thoughtful design principles.
